
CoreXtreme Rules and Guidelines

Welcome to CoreXtreme! To ensure a safe and enjoyable experience for everyone, please adhere to the following rules and guidelines:

1. Respect Others
   - Treat all members and staff with respect. Harassment, discrimination, or disruptive behavior will not be tolerated.

2. Be Punctual
   - Arrive on time for classes. If you are late, please join the class quietly without disturbing others.

3. Proper Attire
   - Wear appropriate workout attire and supportive shoes. Avoid wearing jeans or any clothing that may restrict movement.

4. Personal Hygiene
   - Maintain good personal hygiene. Please ensure you are clean and have used deodorant before attending classes.

5. Equipment Use
   - Use equipment properly and return it to its designated place after use. If you notice any equipment that is damaged or malfunctioning, please report it to a staff member.

6. Follow Trainer Instructions
   - Listen to your trainer's instructions and guidance during classes. If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to ask your trainer for assistance.

7. Limit Cell Phone Use
   - Please minimize cell phone use in the workout area to maintain a focused and respectful environment.

8. Stay Hydrated
   - Bring a water bottle to stay hydrated during your workouts. We encourage regular water breaks.

9. Injury Reporting**
   - If you sustain an injury or feel unwell during a class, inform your trainer immediately and seek assistance.

10. Cancellation Policy
    - Respect our cancellation policy for classes and memberships. Please notify us in advance if you cannot attend a scheduled class.

11. Child Supervision
    - Children under the age of 14 must be supervised by an adult at all times in the facility.

12. Photography and Videography
    - Please refrain from taking photos or videos of other members without their consent. Always respect the privacy of others.

By following these rules, you contribute to a positive atmosphere at CoreXtreme. Thank you for your cooperation, and we look forward to seeing you in class!

If you have any questions or concerns about these rules, please do not hesitate to reach out to our staff.
